      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enables notification to a host application that a modal dialog is displayed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>Some applications that host designers need to be notified when a modal dialog box has been invoked.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>Visual Studio is an example of such a host.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>The <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Activities.Presentation.IModalService&gt;</ph> interface provides an interface to communicate the current modal status.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>The Windows Workflow Designer calls the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Activities.Presentation.IModalService.SetModalState%2A&gt;</ph> method.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>When the <ph id="ph1">`isModal`</ph> parameter is set to <ph id="ph2">`true`</ph>, the host is notified that a modal dialog is displayed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>This is an optional service.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>If a host application does not care about the modal status,  you need not use the service.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>In the current implementation, if a Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) message box (which is a modal dialog) is invoked, the <ph id="ph1">&lt;xref:System.Activities.Presentation.IModalService.SetModalState%2A&gt;</ph>is not called.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT">
          <source>If the host application requires this information, another workaround must be created.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Notifies the host application that a modal dialog is being displayed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If set to <ph id="ph1">`true`</ph>, a modal dialog is being displayed.</source>
        </trans-unit>
